cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL 

The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques applied to text data. Specifically, it focuses on distributional semantics and clustering of documents in a bilingual comparable corpus. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for clustering documents, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely sub-category. The use of neural word embeddings and linear transformations falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's use of neural models and deep learning techniques makes cs.DL (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category as well.
